name: KALW:
Impact:
Dovetail has turned out to be more than just a tool for us. Because of the way that you've supported us in the transition, it's helped us strengthen our creator community. We have in-house podcasts, but we also work with teams that operate mostly independently. We're able to offer them so much more now, which has allowed us to expand our podcast network into something more robust. Having a tool that truly meets our needs is the glue.
- Shereen Adel, Director of Impact, KALW Public Media

name: Thank you to PRX supporters in
Primary Market: all other locations around the world.

name: Why you listen to
Impact:
Thank you for the beautiful stories.
- Joanne K. (Albuquerque, NM), Ear Hustle supporter

name: Why you listen to
Impact:
The work you do is important, we need more empathy in the world.
- Emma P. (Altoona, IA), Ear Hustle supporter

name: Why you listen to
Impact:
I really enjoy listening to your podcast every evening. Keep up the good work. You give a perspective that I cannot find elsewhere.
- Dorothy M. (Amherst, MA), The World supporter

name: Why you listen to
Impact:
I really appreciate the This Day podcast. Fantastic, educational and fun content.
- Chadwick W. (Appleton, WI), Radiotopia supporter

name: Why you listen to
Impact:
I love that your news show lives up to its name: Truly, we can hear stories that encompass so many more places than the usual news broadcast. I also appreciate that you don't only cover the tragedies but include some much-needed uplift. My gratitude to the entire team.
- Anonymous (Arlington, VA), The World supporter

name: Why you listen to
Impact:
Please keep up the balanced and extensive coverage of world news. I listen to you daily ... You are one of the few news sources that I trust.
- Vijaya S. (Atlanta, GA), The World supporter

name: Why you listen to
Impact:
Big thanks to the entire team at The World for your journalism and truth seeking on a global scale. You have been bringing me news and culture (to include excellent music) from around the globe since I started listening in 2001. Keep doing it, please.
- Venecia K. (Austin, TX), The World supporter

name: Why you listen to
Impact:
Nate, just discovering your show and I'm in love. Your voice, your storytelling skills, your timing. It's all fantastic. Thank you so much.
- Thomas O. (Bethesda, MD), The Memory Palace supporter

name: Why you listen to
Impact:
I have listened from the first episode. I have turned on coworkers and my son and daughter to Ear Hustle. We all love the show.
- Veronica B. (Birmingham, AL), Ear Hustle supporter

name: Why you listen to
Impact:
I've listened to every episode and love the show. Thanks for your amazing storytelling.
- Jennifer B. (Bloomington, IN), Ear Hustle supporter

name: Why you listen to
Impact:
The work you do is vitally important. As a long time listener, I can honestly say the stories you share have made me a better person.
- Heide H. (Boise, ID), Ear Hustle supporter

name: Why you listen to
Impact:
Thank you for this amazing show! It's on my must listen to list.
- James B. (Chandler, AZ), This Day supporter

name: Why you listen to
Impact:
Keep up the solid journalism work you do and provide!
Anonymous (Charlotte, NC), PRX supporter

name: Why you listen to
Impact:
Over the years, Radiotopia has changed my life. I owe so much of my growth and understanding to the Memory Palace, 99%, Theory, Radio Diaries, The Truth, Strangers - my god so many amazing things. This is a small amount but it's what I can do now. Please keep making magic.
- Nick B. (Columbia, SC), Radiotopia supporter

name: Why you listen to
Impact:
Love, love, LOVED the serial show Appearances! Thank you for such a beautiful, thoughtful, funny, and touching experience.
- Melina B. (Englewood, CO), PRX supporter

name: Why you listen to
Impact:
Love the show ÔøΩ as do the students I teach at a correctional facility in North Carolina.
- Sherry T. (Fuquay Varina, NC), Ear Hustle supporter

name: Why you listen to
Impact:
I wish it could be more! Thank you all for all you do and all you are. Sending love and hugs xo
- Jody B. (Halifax, NS, Canada), Ear Hustle supporter

name: Why you listen to
Impact:
I am a believer in free public access to news and commend you on your extraordinary work. Thank you so very much.
- Helen M. (Halton Hills, ON, Canada), The World supporter

name: Why you listen to
Impact:
I have been listening since the beginning and love Ear Hustle.
- Leaf S. (Hancock, NH), Ear Hustle supporter

name: Why you listen to
Impact:
Beautifully crafted art pieces of hope, emotion, kindness, differences. Thank you for softening my heart each episode.
- Arthur M. (Kensington, CA), The Memory Palace supporter

name: Why you listen to
Impact:
Ear Hustle is a big part of the reason I teach college mathematics in a state prison in Ohio. The first person in the prison to earn a bachelor's degree while incarcerated graduated last summer, and several more have graduated since then. Your podcast opened my eyes to the resilience of the human spirit in carceral environments.
- Darci K. (Kent, OH), Ear Hustle supporter

name: Why you listen to
Impact:
I want to thank you for the impact your podcast has had on me, especially thank you to Earlonne for his insights especially in the episodes from death row and revisiting George Floyd and his explanation of how sentencing works ... I hope I have become a kinder, more compassionate human because of your podcast which sometimes stays with me for days and weeks after I listen to an episode. Appreciate you so much.
- Anonymous (Knoxville, TN), Ear Hustle supporter

name: Why you listen to
Impact:
This podcast is the best. Thank you for your creativity, humor and inventiveness in thinking about what stories to cover next. I'm particularly impressed and moved by the times you've gone out into world to find something that an incarcerated person had found meaningful, and then went back to report to them what the experience was like. That's an amazing gift.
- Sara B. (Laramie, WY), Ear Hustle supporter

name: Why you listen to
Impact:
There's not much I could say that you haven't heard before but I sincerely appreciate you passion and authenticity. I love when people challenge standard beliefs and change antiquated perceptions and you all do it beautifully. ... Thank you to everyone on the show for all your blood, sweat and tears. You are making change in the world for the better.
- Megan S. (Las Vegas, NV), Ear Hustle supporter

name: Why you listen to
Impact:
I am grateful for EarHustle. You have broadened my understanding and deepened my compassion.
- Donna G. (Lincoln, NE), Ear Hustle supporter

name: Why you listen to
Impact:
I've been listening to your stellar program for a number of years. So grateful for your insights and potent storytelling. Your team helps us understand the facets of our world through the lens of the environment, politics, art, and culture. It's about connection -- so much intelligence and wit, generosity and heart that moves through each broadcast. Public radio/media is a powerful community resource, and this public space is so enriched with your presence. Thank you for providing us these connections across this beautiful planet of ours. You are so deeply appreciated!
- Jessica E. (Makawao, HI), The World supporter

name: Why you listen to
Impact:
I absolutely adore The Memory Palace and Normal Gossip. When Normal Gossip was describing their management move I just knew they were going to say they were going to Radiotopia. This is the place for audio programs because they're all exactly what the artists want them to be. They're completely sincere and genuine and I love it!
-Hannah K. (Minneapolis, MN), Radiotopia supporter

name: Why you listen to
Impact:
Thank you for all the wonderful journalism and journalists on the The World Team. You are my go to source for informative and unbiased global news.
- Jane V. (Murray River, PE, Canada), The World supporter

name: Why you listen to
Impact:
It is essential to have reporters on the ground giving us an unbiased look at the important stories from every region of our planet.
- Anonymous (Pass Christian, MS) The World supporter
